						               													<description>Jurors, will you make the right decision?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Christmas dinner, a Breton family and the body of an accountant found at the bottom of a cliff.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What happened at the Duguenecs that night?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Slip into the shoes of a juror, judge a criminal case and deliver your verdict.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO PLAY ?&amp;#10;1. Perform the requested actions according to the indications and the order of the 12 Juror Cards&amp;#10;2. Reveal the 4 fact sheets throughout the game and start the debate!&amp;#10;3. Cast your verdict by voting anonymously with the Final Vote Cards. Guilty or Not Guilty?&amp;#10;4. Discover the Final Revelation&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play with friends for an evening by recreating the atmosphere of a closed session! Or make the fun last by revealing only a few items a day!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Content:&amp;#10;- 1 Rule of the game&amp;#10;- 1 Portrait of the accused &amp;amp; her statement&amp;#10;- 1 Scene of the crime&amp;#10;- 12 Juror Cards&amp;#10;- 1 Discovery Pass&amp;#10;- 24 Final Voting Cards&amp;#10;- 3 sealed fact sheets&amp;#10;- 1 FINAL REVELATION! To reveal at the end of the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Intime conviction is a craft object entirely designed, made and assembled by hand and in Belgium. The format of the game is unusual as well: this game is in an envelope.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
